# Coding Standards

## Clarity over cleverness

Write code the way JobJitsu speaks: precise, calm, inspectable. Prefer boring explicitness over magic.

```
✅ GOOD: approveSend(applicationId)  // user-gated outbound
❌ BAD:  smartAutopilot.blastAll()   // volume + hidden control
```

## Naming (user + code)

Use canonical product nouns from `docs/brand/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`:

| Use in UI | Avoid in UI |
|-----------|-------------|
| Agent, Application, Queue, Follow-up, Preferences, On-device | LLM, Bot, Autopilot, Opp, “AI magic” |

Internal/code may use `AiProvider`, `locality`, etc. User-visible strings follow the **branding-development** rule (Agent, not LLM).

Components: `Jj{Domain}{Element}` (e.g. `JjApplicationQueueRow`, `JjAgentPrivacyPill`).

## Privacy in code

- No accidental logging of résumé bodies, tokens, or full application letters to remote sinks.
- Feature flags must not enable cloud résumé storage by default.
- Network calls that transmit career data need an obvious call site and **human-approved** path.

## UI & copy in code

- Sentence case; calm, encouraging voice (`docs/brand/VOICE_AND_TONE.md`, `COPY_GUIDELINES.md`).
- Never pressure (no FOMO, guilt, streaks).
- Errors: plain recovery language — no metaphor, no blame (`ERROR_MESSAGES.md`).
- Success: quiet confirmation — no streak/guilt metrics (`SUCCESS_MESSAGES.md`).
- One job per view; uncluttered layout.
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`; no confetti or urgency animations.

## Defaults that match philosophy

- Approval-before-send on by default for high-stakes outbound.
- On-device intelligence path as primary.
- Sound off for notifications by default.

## Dependencies

Prefer open, auditable libraries. Do not add analytics SDKs that exfiltrate career content. If network telemetry is ever required for crash reports, strip PII and document it plainly.
